# Changelog

## [Part 2] CSS Styling & Responsive Design - May 16 to May 27, 2026

### May 16, 2026

#### Added
- Created external CSS file (style.css) and linked to all HTML pages
- Added CSS reset for cross-browser consistency (`* { margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing }`)

#### Changed
- Set body background color to match requirements

---

### May 17, 2026

#### Added
- Added typography scale using rem units (h1: 2.5rem, h2: 2rem, h3: 1.75rem, h4: 1.5rem, p: 1rem)
- Added Google Fonts integration (Lora for headings, Open Sans for body)

#### Fixed
- Corrected font family declarations across all pages

---

### May 18, 2026

#### Added
- Added CSS Grid layout for desktop (3-column grid using `grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr)`)
- Added 2-column grid layout for secondary pages

#### Changed
- Updated navigation bar background to light peachy-pink (#FFB6A4)
- Changed navigation text color to white (#FFFFFF)
- Changed navigation font to 'Lora', serif

---

### May 19, 2026

#### Added
- Added hover pseudo-class effects for navigation buttons (background change, transform)
- Added active pseudo-class effects (scale transform)
- Added focus pseudo-class for accessibility (outline on focus)

#### Fixed
- Removed duplicate .brand-heading selectors (was defined 3 times)
- Removed duplicate .social-icons selectors (was defined twice)

---

### May 20, 2026

#### Added
- Added responsive breakpoints:
  - Desktop: > 1024px (3 columns)
  - Tablet: 768px - 1024px (2 columns)
  - Mobile: < 768px (1 column, stacked navigation)
  - Small mobile: < 480px (extra adjustments)

#### Changed
- Standardized inconsistent breakpoints (was 780px, 760px, 700px, 650px, 620px → now 1024px, 768px, 480px)

---

### May 21, 2026

#### Added
- Added relative units (rem for fonts, % for widths) for responsive design
- Added responsive image support (`max-width: 100%; height: auto;`)

#### Changed
- Converted pixel-based font sizes to rem-based typography scale

---

### May 22, 2026

#### Changed
- Unified navigation bar styling across all pages (Home, About, Menu, Promotions, Contact)
- Made peachy-pink navigation consistent throughout website

#### Fixed
- Corrected menu page grid display issue (items now display in proper grid layout)
- Fixed category filter buttons styling

---

### May 23, 2026

#### Changed
- Applied Peach Puff (#FFDAB9) background color to all pages consistently

#### Fixed
- Removed conflicting background gradients that overrode the peach color
- Ensured body background applies to all pages

---

### May 24, 2026

#### Added
- Added CSS Grid examples to demonstrate layout requirements
- Added flexbox components for consistent spacing

#### Fixed
- Fixed menu item card sizing (consistent width of 280px)
- Fixed quantity control buttons styling

---

### May 25, 2026

#### Changed
- Updated all navigation links to use consistent hover effects
- Improved mobile navigation (stacks vertically on screens < 768px)

#### Fixed
- Resolved issue with multi-column to single-column transition on mobile

---

### May 26, 2026

#### Added
- Created screenshots folder for evidence
- Took screenshots of website on:
  - Desktop (1920×1080) - 3-column layout
  - Tablet (768×1024) - 2-column layout
  - Mobile (375×667) - 1-column layout, stacked navigation

#### Changed
- Updated README.md with screenshot links and changelog

---

### May 27, 2026

#### Added
- Added final documentation to README.md:
  - Changelog entries for all changes
  - Screenshot evidence with paths
  - Testing checklist

#### Fixed
- Corrected screenshot file paths in README.md
- Fixed folder structure (moved screenshots to main level)

#### Changed
- Moved style.css from css folder to main project folder
- Deleted empty css folder
- Consolidated CHANGELOG content into README.md

---

